    <!--               SECTION THREE: SECTORS & SEGMENTS                 -->
    <!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════ -->

    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDef_15">• Sector: The portion of a circle bounded by two radii and one of the arcs they intercept.
\n • Segment: The region of a circle bounded by a chord and the arc subtended by that chord.</string>

    <!-- Q: Is a sector bounded by two radii and an arc? Answer: True -->
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDefQuestion_15">Is a sector bounded by two radii and an arc?</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDefAnswerOne_15">True</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDefAnswerTwo_15">False</string>
    <!-- Only 2 answers for True/False — third answer intentionally removed -->
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDefAnswerThree_15"></string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryDefCorrectAnswer_15">True</string>

    <!-- Fixed typo: S=πR^15 → S=πR² -->
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryProperties_15">• Circle Area Formula: Computed by the formula S=πR².
\n • Area of a Sector: Calculated as S=[(πR²)/360°]*α, where α is the degree measure of the central angle.
\n • Area of a Segment: Computed by S=[(πR²)/360°]*α−S△, where S△ is the area of the triangle formed by the centre and the chord\'s endpoints.</string>

    <!-- Q: Area of a sector with R=6 and α=90°? Answer: 9π -->
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryPropsQuestion_15">What is the area of a sector with radius R = 6 and central angle α = 90° (leave answer in terms of π)?</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryPropsAnswerOne_15">36π</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryPropsAnswerTwo_15">9π</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryPropsAnswerThree_15">3π</string>
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryPropsCorrectAnswer_15">9π</string>

    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryWorkedExamples_15">• Area of a full circle with R = 5: S = π × 5² = 25π ≈ 78.54.
\n • Area of a sector with R = 6 and central angle α = 90°: S = (π × 36 / 360°) × 90° = 36π / 4 = 9π ≈ 28.27.
\n • Area of a segment with R = 6 and α = 90°: the triangle formed is a right isosceles triangle with legs 6, so S△ = ½ × 6 × 6 = 18. Segment area = 9π − 18 ≈ 10.27.</string>

    <!-- Q: Area of full circle with R=5? Answer: 25π -->
    <string name="SectionThreeTheoryWorkedExQuestion_15">What is the area of a circle with radius R = 5 (leave answer in terms of π)?</string>
